# 📈 AI Investment Decision Engine

An end-to-end machine learning platform for stock selection, portfolio analytics, explainable AI, and automated investment research reports.

The system combines financial fundamentals, machine learning classification, SHAP explainability, and portfolio backtesting into an interactive Streamlit dashboard.

---

# 🚀 Features

## 🤖 Machine Learning Stock Selection

The engine uses a Logistic Regression pipeline:

- StandardScaler preprocessing
- Classification model
- BUY / HOLD prediction
- Probability scoring

Example output:

| Symbol | Probability | Signal |
|---|---:|---|
| NVDA | 94% | BUY |
| MSFT | 94% | BUY |
| GOOGL | 97% | BUY |

---

# 🧠 Explainable AI (SHAP)

The model is fully explainable using SHAP values.

For every stock the system identifies:

### Positive Drivers

- Profitability metrics
- Cash flow quality
- Business efficiency

### Negative Drivers

- Valuation risk
- Financial risk factors

Example:


NVDA

Positive contributors:

operatingMargin
freeCashFlowPerShare

Negative contributors:

peRatio

---

# 📊 Portfolio Backtesting

The platform compares the AI portfolio against SPY.

Metrics:

- Annual Return
- Annual Volatility
- Sharpe Ratio
- Maximum Drawdown

Example:

| Portfolio | Return | Sharpe | Drawdown |
|---|---:|---:|---:|
| AI Portfolio | 14.1% | 0.94 | -26.7% |
| SPY | 11.4% | 0.66 | -25.3% |

---

# 📉 Risk Analytics

The dashboard provides:

- Equity curve comparison
- Drawdown analysis
- Risk-adjusted performance

---

# 🖥️ Interactive Dashboard

Built with Streamlit.

Available pages:

## 📊 Portfolio

Displays:

- Performance metrics
- Portfolio statistics
- Benchmark comparison


## 🤖 ML Signals

Shows:

- Stock predictions
- Probability scores
- Trading signals


## 🧠 Explainability

Provides:

- Feature importance
- SHAP charts
- Model reasoning


## 🔍 Stock Analysis

Individual company research page:

- Company profile
- Financial quality metrics
- AI recommendation
- Analyst summary
- SHAP drivers


## 📄 AI Research Report

Automatically generates PDF investment reports including:

- Investment thesis
- Financial metrics
- Model prediction
- Explainability results

